  "prompt": "Is the test taker report for GMAT accessible immediately after the test ? It\u2019s not the official score report that GMAC sends after 15-20 days.",
  "response": "Yes, immediately after completing the GMAT, test takers can access **unofficial scores** for the Quantitative and Verbal sections, as well as the Integrated Reasoning section. Here's a breakdown of what you can expect:\n\n1. **Immediately After the Test:**\n   - **Quantitative Section Score:** You'll see your score for the Quant section right after you finish it.\n   - **Verbal Section Score:** Similarly, your Verbal section score is available immediately after completion.\n   - **Integrated Reasoning Score:** This score is also provided right after completing its section.\n   - **Total GMAT Score:** Based on the Quant and Verbal scores, you'll receive an unofficial total score.\n\n2. **After the Exam:**\n   - **Analytical Writing Assessment (AWA) Score:** The AWA score is **not** available immediately. Instead, it is part of the official score report that GMAC sends out.\n   - **Official Score Report:** Comprehensive scores, including the AWA and a detailed breakdown of all sections, are typically available **within 15-20 days** after your test date. You can access these through your GMAT account online once they're released.\n\n3. **Score Verification and Sending:**\n   - While you have access to unofficial scores right away, the official scores are crucial for sending to business schools. Ensure that your contact information is up-to-date so you receive the official report promptly.\n\n**Additional Tips:**\n- **Review During the Test:** Take advantage of the opportunity to review your answers during the test. You can skip questions and return to them later within each section's allotted time.\n- **Check Your GMAT Account:** Regularly log into your GMAT account for updates on your official scores and any additional information regarding your test.\n\nIf you have any concerns or don't see your unofficial scores immediately after completing the test, it's a good idea to reach out to GMAC's customer service for assistance.",
